text: Philipp Mißfelder (August 25, 1979 – July 13, 2015) was a German politician and a member of the Bundestag. From January through March 2014 he served in the German government as the Coordinator for Transatlantic Cooperation in the Field of Intersocietal Relations, Cultural and Information Policy. ==References== Category:1979 births Category:2015 deaths Category:Deaths from pulmonary embolism Category:Members of the German Bundestag Category:German historians Category:People from Gelsenkirchen Category:Politicians from North Rhine-Westphalia Category:Politicians of the Christian Democratic Union of Germany
